1
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:54,200
What did you do to my sister?

2
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:55,960
Fahsai.

3
00:02:56,600 --> 00:02:57,680
- You!
- Fahsai.

4
00:02:59,320 --> 00:03:01,000
- Dad!
- Black Doc.

5
00:03:02,560 --> 00:03:03,840
Wayu?

6
00:03:05,080 --> 00:03:06,520
You were planning to expose me with this?

7
00:03:10,720 --> 00:03:11,680
- Dad!
- Ms. Maysa.

8
00:03:11,760 --> 00:03:12,920
- Dad!
- Ms. Maysa, don't go in.

9
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:15,080
Are you going to leave
without even telling me

10
00:03:16,280 --> 00:03:18,000
that you're Peeraka?

11
00:03:20,160 --> 00:03:23,680
<i>You also want to sleep with men</i>
<i>who have good profiles,</i>

12
00:03:24,440 --> 00:03:25,920
<i>just like my clients.</i>

13
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:26,880
Oh?

14
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:28,720
Before becoming Prime Minister,

15
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:30,120
- become a decent human being first.
- Yes.

16
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:31,440
Right?

17
00:03:31,520 --> 00:03:32,640
How could you do this?

18
00:03:32,720 --> 00:03:34,280
I'm not answering any questions.

19
00:03:34,360 --> 00:03:36,240
Everyone, everyone.

20
00:03:36,320 --> 00:03:37,760
This is the police.

21
00:03:38,560 --> 00:03:41,240
Mr. Mahasamut Pasukampanart,

22
00:03:41,320 --> 00:03:43,400
step out and give your statement
to the authorities.

23
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:45,360
Where is Mahasamut?

24
00:03:49,720 --> 00:03:50,560
Here, boss.

25
00:03:51,640 --> 00:03:53,160
Head to Sa Kaeo first.

26
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:57,280
I've got Cherd waiting for you there.
He'll take you across the border.

27
00:03:57,960 --> 00:03:59,640
Once things quiet down, you can come back.

28
00:04:01,160 --> 00:04:02,400
Go down this way.

29
00:04:03,480 --> 00:04:05,840
I already prepared clothes
and a motorcycle for you.

30
00:04:05,920 --> 00:04:09,000
But you have to leave through the back.
I'll handle the rest.

31
00:04:33,080 --> 00:04:35,080
WAYU

32
00:04:37,280 --> 00:04:39,440
We got played. Spread the word.

33
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:41,400
Tell everyone to report his location
if they spot him.

34
00:04:41,480 --> 00:04:42,680
Okay, bro.

35
00:04:46,200 --> 00:04:48,280
EVERYONE, MP SAMUT ESCAPED ARREST

36
00:04:48,360 --> 00:04:50,360
IF YOU SPOT A SUSPICIOUS PERSON
RIDING A BIG BIKE

37
00:04:50,440 --> 00:04:52,560
REPORT IT TO THE MAD DOG PAGE IMMEDIATELY

38
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:56,160
EVERYONE, MP SAMUT ESCAPED ARREST

39
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:57,120
IF YOU SPOT A SUSPICIOUS PERSON
RIDING A BIG BIKE

40
00:04:57,200 --> 00:04:58,160
REPORT IT TO THE MAD DOG PAGE IMMEDIATELY

41
00:05:14,800 --> 00:05:15,640
- Yong.
- Ms. Fahsai.

42
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:17,720
I need to go take care of something.
Please take care of Dad for me.

43
00:05:17,800 --> 00:05:18,880
Where are you going?

44
00:05:18,960 --> 00:05:20,200
I'll explain later.

45
00:05:20,280 --> 00:05:23,960
You and Dad can't watch TV,
check social media, or anything like that.

46
00:05:24,040 --> 00:05:26,840
Why?

47
00:05:27,840 --> 00:05:29,600
A netizen just sent this in.

48
00:05:29,680 --> 00:05:30,680
EVERYONE, KEEP YOUR EYES OPEN
HAVE YOU SPOTTED HIM?

49
00:05:30,760 --> 00:05:31,680
THAT BIKE LOOKS FAMILIAR

50
00:05:31,760 --> 00:05:32,720
HEY, THERE HE IS. HE JUST RODE PAST HERE

51
00:05:33,360 --> 00:05:36,000
Hey, the suspect's on the move.

52
00:05:38,280 --> 00:05:41,120
I MADE IT TO MAD DOG'S LIVESTREAM

53
00:05:41,200 --> 00:05:43,960
REALLY? LET ME HELP TOO

54
00:05:44,040 --> 00:05:46,800
YOU GUYS HAVE EAGLE EYES
I'M GOING OUTSIDE TO HELP LOOK TOO

55
00:05:47,440 --> 00:05:49,400
Looking at these two locations,

56
00:05:49,480 --> 00:05:51,920
it lines up perfectly. It has to be him.

57
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:56,120
PLEASE CATCH HIM

58
00:05:56,200 --> 00:05:57,800
FOUND HIM

59
00:05:57,880 --> 00:05:59,080
Tips are pouring in.

60
00:06:00,640 --> 00:06:03,520
Thank you, everyone,
for not letting evil people walk free.

61
00:06:10,400 --> 00:06:11,600
Which direction is he heading?

62
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:14,480
Okay. Thanks.

63
00:06:26,880 --> 00:06:30,920
The Mad Dog page said
that bastard MP escaped this way.

64
00:06:32,400 --> 00:06:33,240
Look.

65
00:06:35,440 --> 00:06:38,600
There. The bike and clothes match exactly.

66
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:45,920
Hey, that's Pitbull.

67
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:47,640
Hurry up and send them the location.

68
00:07:02,520 --> 00:07:05,680
The suspect is heading toward
the intersection. Set up a checkpoint.

69
00:07:46,080 --> 00:07:48,080
<i>Unit 24 calling Unit 15.</i>

70
00:07:48,160 --> 00:07:50,320
<i>The suspect disappeared</i>
<i>from the main road.</i>

71
00:07:50,400 --> 00:07:52,960
<i>We believe he turned into an alley</i>
<i>somewhere along the route. Over.</i>

72
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:54,800
Roger that.

73
00:08:57,800 --> 00:08:59,720
Why are you so obsessed
with ruining my life?

74
00:09:01,440 --> 00:09:02,920
Why the hell wouldn't I be?

75
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:11,400
Wayu.

76
00:09:21,760 --> 00:09:22,960
Come here.

77
00:09:40,680 --> 00:09:41,680
Camera ready.

78
00:09:42,440 --> 00:09:44,000
All right, everyone.

79
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:48,000
We're about to find out
where the suspect,

80
00:09:48,080 --> 00:09:49,200
Mr. Mahasamut, is hiding.

81
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:52,160
What does that mean? A livestream?

82
00:09:52,240 --> 00:09:53,440
Yeah.

83
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:55,680
Mad Dog already knows.
They knew before the police did.

84
00:09:55,760 --> 00:09:56,600
Wow.

85
00:09:56,680 --> 00:09:57,880
That's badass.

86
00:10:04,680 --> 00:10:06,120
Let's start.

87
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:08,480
YOU FOUND HIM. PITBULL IS SO BADASS

88
00:10:08,560 --> 00:10:09,880
WHERE IS IT?

89
00:10:09,960 --> 00:10:10,920
BETTER THAN THE POLICE

90
00:10:14,360 --> 00:10:15,200
MAD DOG IS AMAZING

91
00:10:15,280 --> 00:10:17,040
ARE YOU 007?

92
00:10:17,120 --> 00:10:18,800
BE CAREFUL. I'M ROOTING FOR YOU

93
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:44,640
Turn yourself in.

94
00:10:48,360 --> 00:10:49,560
There's no way you're getting away.

95
00:10:54,520 --> 00:10:55,720
Do you remember

96
00:10:56,720 --> 00:10:59,600
August 10, 2018?

97
00:11:01,480 --> 00:11:03,800
You and your men stormed
the Jaiaree house.

98
00:11:06,040 --> 00:11:07,320
You beat

99
00:11:07,960 --> 00:11:10,160
and stabbed two women to death
in their own home.

100
00:11:12,760 --> 00:11:14,520
One of them was a reporter

101
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:17,920
who knew the truth
about your hellish club.

102
00:11:20,040 --> 00:11:22,200
The other was that reporter's mother.

103
00:11:24,640 --> 00:11:26,520
You tried to kill her son too.

104
00:11:27,440 --> 00:11:30,280
<i>But a neighbor walked in,</i>
<i>so that boy managed to escape.</i>

105
00:11:31,120 --> 00:11:32,120
CAN YOU JUST SHOOT HIM?

106
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:33,160
YES. YOU SHOULDN'T LET HIM LIVE

107
00:11:33,240 --> 00:11:34,640
You shot that neighbor,

108
00:11:35,640 --> 00:11:37,880
then burned the house down
to destroy the evidence.

109
00:11:40,480 --> 00:11:44,560
You framed that boy
for murdering his own mother and sister.

110
00:11:48,200 --> 00:11:49,960
How does Wayu know about this?

111
00:11:51,080 --> 00:11:52,480
Who the hell are you?

112
00:11:56,320 --> 00:11:58,800
I'm the guy you pointed
a gun at that night.

113
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:05,440
You know what this is, don't you?

114
00:12:05,520 --> 00:12:06,880
- Go!
- Hey!

115
00:12:06,960 --> 00:12:08,520
Raka, run!

116
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:09,480
Run!

117
00:12:12,960 --> 00:12:14,280
Kul!

118
00:12:14,360 --> 00:12:15,600
Kul!

119
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:17,480
Kul!

120
00:12:22,640 --> 00:12:23,920
Raka?

121
00:12:38,880 --> 00:12:42,880
You want to know why I became Wayu

122
00:12:42,960 --> 00:12:45,280
and have been haunting you all this time?

123
00:12:45,960 --> 00:12:47,760
Because you're stupid.

124
00:12:49,800 --> 00:12:51,000
You were stupid enough

125
00:12:52,160 --> 00:12:54,960
to let Singha use someone else's body
in place of mine.

126
00:12:57,120 --> 00:13:01,440
You were stupid enough
to let him fool you for six whole years.

127
00:13:09,280 --> 00:13:10,800
Please don't die, Raka.

128
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:13,800
Oh my God, is someone
actually going to die here?

129
00:14:09,480 --> 00:14:10,640
GO TO HELL, SAMUT

130
00:14:13,120 --> 00:14:14,200
SHOOT HIM, PITBULL

131
00:14:14,280 --> 00:14:15,440
WHERE ARE THE POLICE? GO HELP HIM

132
00:14:19,880 --> 00:14:20,920
KILL HIM

133
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:22,040
WHEN WILL THE POLICE GET THERE?
PITBULL'S IN TROUBLE

134
00:14:29,160 --> 00:14:30,080
THE POLICE ARE PROBABLY
STOPPING FOR COFFEE. THEY'LL COME LATER

135
00:14:30,160 --> 00:14:31,080
PITBULL, FIGHT HIM

136
00:14:31,160 --> 00:14:32,560
Hey.

137
00:14:32,640 --> 00:14:33,680
WHAT A WASTE. SOMEONE WITH A FACE
LIKE THAT SHOULDN'T BE BAD

138
00:14:33,760 --> 00:14:34,840
DON'T FEEL BAD FOR HIM. SOMEONE
THIS HORRIBLE DOESN'T DESERVE TO LIVE

139
00:14:40,400 --> 00:14:41,440
Why did it cut out?

140
00:14:43,880 --> 00:14:45,040
Do something.

141
00:14:50,680 --> 00:14:51,520
I can't get it back.

142
00:15:13,520 --> 00:15:16,560
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

143
00:15:17,800 --> 00:15:19,440
- Don't hurt me.
- Why?

144
00:15:20,600 --> 00:15:21,640
Are you afraid to die?

145
00:15:23,800 --> 00:15:25,640
When you killed other people,

146
00:15:26,160 --> 00:15:27,720
did you ever think they'd be afraid too?

147
00:15:29,680 --> 00:15:32,240
You killed my mother and my sister.

148
00:15:35,080 --> 00:15:36,960
Don't take up
any more space in this world.

149
00:16:27,760 --> 00:16:29,080
Go get the bolt cutters.

150
00:16:29,160 --> 00:16:30,040
Let's go.

151
00:16:35,360 --> 00:16:36,560
Samut, stop.

152
00:16:41,280 --> 00:16:42,840
Fahsai. Fahsai.

153
00:16:43,920 --> 00:16:46,480
Stop. Get out of here. Samut has a gun.

154
00:16:47,080 --> 00:16:48,200
And don't you have a gun too?

155
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:51,560
Put the gun away.
I'll talk to Samut myself.

156
00:16:52,240 --> 00:16:53,840
Fahsai. Fahsai.

157
00:16:54,920 --> 00:16:57,440
Raka. Raka, don't.

158
00:16:57,520 --> 00:16:59,560
- Don't go in.
- Fahsai already went after Samut.

159
00:16:59,640 --> 00:17:02,360
Don't go in there.
He'll use Fahsai as leverage against you.

160
00:17:03,640 --> 00:17:04,920
And what if he hurts Fahsai?

161
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:06,200
Don't worry.

162
00:17:06,280 --> 00:17:08,800
I already sent Sergeant Dam around back.
We'll go this way.

163
00:17:11,760 --> 00:17:12,680
Come on. Trust me.

164
00:17:14,880 --> 00:17:15,720
Come on.

165
00:17:51,760 --> 00:17:52,800
Samut.

166
00:17:55,840 --> 00:17:56,680
Fahsai.

167
00:17:59,400 --> 00:18:00,240
What are you doing here?

168
00:18:00,320 --> 00:18:02,280
You got shot, didn't you?

169
00:18:02,360 --> 00:18:05,600
Let's go see a doctor.
I know everything now.

170
00:18:06,560 --> 00:18:08,640
Please surrender to the police.

171
00:18:13,560 --> 00:18:14,400
Raka.

172
00:18:14,480 --> 00:18:15,400
Raka.

173
00:18:16,960 --> 00:18:19,640
We have to do the right thing for once.

174
00:18:21,840 --> 00:18:26,320
There's no other way,
except admitting what we did wrong.

175
00:18:27,880 --> 00:18:31,040
Please surrender, and I'll take you
to the hospital, okay?

176
00:18:31,120 --> 00:18:33,440
Wait, Fahsai, don't believe them.

177
00:18:33,520 --> 00:18:35,480
I didn't do anything wrong.

178
00:18:35,560 --> 00:18:36,560
They framed me.

179
00:18:36,640 --> 00:18:38,480
Stop lying already, Samut.

180
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:42,960
You confessed to everything.

181
00:18:44,080 --> 00:18:47,800
Everyone in the country heard
what you said to Mr. Wayu earlier.

182
00:18:49,040 --> 00:18:51,200
The police have us
completely surrounded now.

183
00:18:58,560 --> 00:19:00,640
I don't have anyone left anymore.

184
00:19:02,320 --> 00:19:04,800
If we did wrong, then we have to admit it.

185
00:19:07,040 --> 00:19:10,120
You're not the only one
who'll go to prison or suffer.

186
00:19:11,440 --> 00:19:15,840
I'll be judged and cursed
by the whole country too.

187
00:19:17,840 --> 00:19:20,320
But I don't care. I'll endure it.

188
00:19:23,920 --> 00:19:26,400
I'll wait for the day you get out…

189
00:19:30,360 --> 00:19:33,160
and then we can come back
and take care of Dad together.

190
00:19:39,200 --> 00:19:40,520
Please, Samut.

191
00:19:48,200 --> 00:19:49,520
I'm sorry.

192
00:19:51,800 --> 00:19:57,080
I thought you hated me
and never wanted to see me again.

193
00:20:02,080 --> 00:20:08,000
I never imagined
we'd ever get to talk like this again.

194
00:20:08,600 --> 00:20:11,200
We only have each other.

195
00:20:13,920 --> 00:20:16,600
How could I abandon you?

196
00:20:18,080 --> 00:20:19,240
I'm sorry.

197
00:20:20,640 --> 00:20:21,920
I'm sorry.

198
00:20:27,480 --> 00:20:29,960
I'm sorry for thinking
terrible things about you.

199
00:20:34,360 --> 00:20:38,160
Even now, I'm still causing
you trouble. I'm sorry.

200
00:20:39,600 --> 00:20:41,120
Don't say anything anymore.

201
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:43,280
Don't say anything.

202
00:20:44,200 --> 00:20:46,800
There's nothing else now. Nothing.

203
00:20:47,320 --> 00:20:49,360
And I'm not suffering at all.

204
00:20:51,360 --> 00:20:53,320
Please surrender to the police.

205
00:20:54,840 --> 00:20:57,240
Just do this for me, for once.

206
00:21:03,440 --> 00:21:05,880
I love you, Samut.

207
00:21:10,880 --> 00:21:12,520
I love you.

208
00:21:29,440 --> 00:21:30,600
Don't say anything anymore.

209
00:21:33,360 --> 00:21:34,760
We'll get through this together.

210
00:21:36,320 --> 00:21:37,240
Well…

211
00:21:39,080 --> 00:21:40,960
I've never regretted

212
00:21:44,240 --> 00:21:45,360
loving you.

213
00:21:49,080 --> 00:21:52,760
Even though it was wrong
and it hurt me so much,

214
00:21:55,160 --> 00:21:56,640
if I had the choice,

215
00:21:57,800 --> 00:22:01,320
I'd want to love you
the way a brother should love his sister.

216
00:22:10,360 --> 00:22:12,880
Then I could've been a better brother.

217
00:22:17,840 --> 00:22:20,000
I could've loved you properly

218
00:22:21,240 --> 00:22:24,680
and never made you suffer
like this again. Understand?

219
00:22:29,760 --> 00:22:30,840
Samut,

220
00:22:31,720 --> 00:22:35,440
you've always been the best brother to me.

221
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:41,080
Let's face this together, okay?

222
00:22:48,840 --> 00:22:50,400
Come with me.

223
00:23:05,120 --> 00:23:07,160
Fahsai. Fahsai.

224
00:23:25,320 --> 00:23:28,880
Samut? Samut.

225
00:23:31,520 --> 00:23:32,880
Samut!

226
00:23:33,880 --> 00:23:36,280
Samut!

227
00:23:44,360 --> 00:23:46,760
No! Samut!

228
00:23:54,480 --> 00:23:55,600
No! Samut!

229
00:23:55,680 --> 00:23:57,480
- Samut.
- Sergeant Dam.

230
00:23:57,560 --> 00:24:01,280
Take photos of every corner of this place,
then radio outside and get forensics here.

231
00:24:02,320 --> 00:24:03,240
Yes, sir.

232
00:24:52,960 --> 00:24:54,280
I will never forgive you.

233
00:24:56,320 --> 00:24:57,520
The sins you committed

234
00:24:58,680 --> 00:25:00,640
will follow you into every lifetime.

235
00:25:23,280 --> 00:25:24,480
May. May.

236
00:25:30,560 --> 00:25:34,760
Thank you for giving us that clip.

237
00:25:37,840 --> 00:25:39,520
It was something I had to do anyway.

238
00:25:42,120 --> 00:25:46,760
I never knew Dad and Samut
did something so horrible to you.

239
00:25:47,960 --> 00:25:49,320
I'm sorry.

240
00:25:50,040 --> 00:25:52,440
I'm truly sorry
for everything that happened.

241
00:25:57,920 --> 00:25:59,120
I also…

242
00:25:59,200 --> 00:26:00,760
When I found out you were still alive,

243
00:26:03,080 --> 00:26:04,200
I was shocked too.

244
00:26:06,200 --> 00:26:10,000
I never imagined
I'd been fooled by you all this time.

245
00:26:11,760 --> 00:26:13,680
At first, I wanted to be angry with you.

246
00:26:16,200 --> 00:26:19,240
But when I thought
about all the pain you carried alone,

247
00:26:20,200 --> 00:26:21,680
I just couldn't.

248
00:26:26,040 --> 00:26:27,360
I'm really glad…

249
00:26:36,960 --> 00:26:38,080
that you survived.

250
00:26:40,720 --> 00:26:42,280
And I'm glad…

251
00:26:44,960 --> 00:26:46,600
we once loved each other.

252
00:28:07,560 --> 00:28:10,240
So, what are you going to do now?

253
00:28:12,520 --> 00:28:14,360
I want to spend
some time alone for a while.

254
00:28:15,080 --> 00:28:18,360
I'll probably travel somewhere far away.

255
00:28:21,320 --> 00:28:24,040
Congratulations in advance, Raka.

256
00:28:25,760 --> 00:28:27,960
I hope you'll be happy

257
00:28:29,480 --> 00:28:31,760
with the person you love forever.

258
00:28:41,840 --> 00:28:46,000
DROP-OFF

259
00:29:01,440 --> 00:29:02,680
Dad.

260
00:29:06,600 --> 00:29:08,600
I miss you.

261
00:29:13,040 --> 00:29:15,960
I want you to come back to me.

262
00:29:23,720 --> 00:29:25,480
Please get better soon.

263
00:29:30,840 --> 00:29:33,160
Can you hear me, Dad?

264
00:29:43,240 --> 00:29:44,800
Dad…

265
00:30:02,600 --> 00:30:03,880
Dad?

266
00:30:07,120 --> 00:30:08,160
Dad?

267
00:30:09,800 --> 00:30:11,040
Dad?

268
00:30:11,640 --> 00:30:13,520
Dad?

269
00:30:13,600 --> 00:30:15,240
Dad, can you hear me?

270
00:30:15,320 --> 00:30:17,080
Dad.

271
00:30:17,960 --> 00:30:19,520
Dad, can you hear me?

272
00:30:19,600 --> 00:30:21,240
Dad.

273
00:30:22,120 --> 00:30:23,160
Dad.

274
00:30:32,280 --> 00:30:33,280
Dad…

275
00:32:30,680 --> 00:32:32,760
Are you really leaving, Ms. Fahsai?

276
00:32:33,640 --> 00:32:35,280
There's nothing left to worry about.

277
00:32:36,080 --> 00:32:38,760
- And what about Mr. Wayu--
- If you're coming with me,

278
00:32:39,800 --> 00:32:41,040
don't mention him again.

279
00:32:42,600 --> 00:32:44,000
Okay.

280
00:32:49,600 --> 00:32:50,680
Hey.

281
00:32:51,800 --> 00:32:53,160
Why do you all look so gloomy?

282
00:32:55,200 --> 00:32:56,960
We should be happy.

283
00:32:58,440 --> 00:33:00,200
Even though the Mad Dog page is gone,

284
00:33:00,280 --> 00:33:03,360
there are now tons of pages exposing
corruption all over social media.

285
00:33:05,400 --> 00:33:07,040
People wanted to become like us.

286
00:33:13,160 --> 00:33:17,720
It's finally time for us
to seriously step away.

287
00:33:21,760 --> 00:33:24,720
Sam, did you submit
your university application yet?

288
00:33:26,800 --> 00:33:30,000
Pa, did you find a location
for your restaurant yet?

289
00:33:30,880 --> 00:33:32,520
I'm still looking around.

290
00:33:35,480 --> 00:33:36,920
I already checked out the farm.

291
00:33:37,000 --> 00:33:39,920
The vegetables are growing well.
I'll harvest some and send them over.

292
00:33:47,720 --> 00:33:48,960
Thanks a lot, Ya,

293
00:33:49,560 --> 00:33:51,440
for helping with everything.

294
00:33:54,280 --> 00:33:57,840
If I didn't help,
you wouldn't pay my salary.

295
00:33:59,720 --> 00:34:01,040
Thank you so much

296
00:34:02,120 --> 00:34:04,480
for bringing us together
to create the Mad Dog page.

297
00:34:05,480 --> 00:34:08,880
I'll never forget
that once in my life,

298
00:34:08,960 --> 00:34:10,679
I got to do something this meaningful.

299
00:34:13,280 --> 00:34:15,400
You made that sound so touching.
What am I supposed to say after that?

300
00:34:15,480 --> 00:34:18,159
Then don't say anything. Just bark.

301
00:34:18,239 --> 00:34:19,400
Like this?

302
00:34:22,880 --> 00:34:26,560
Alright.
Before we all go our separate ways,

303
00:34:26,639 --> 00:34:28,719
our page has a little gift for everyone.

304
00:34:42,360 --> 00:34:45,960
Help me look. How much is it?

305
00:34:46,040 --> 00:34:50,040
Tens, hundreds, thousands, ten-thousands,
hundred-thousands, millions… Ten million.

306
00:34:50,120 --> 00:34:52,280
Eight digits means ten million, bro.

307
00:34:54,600 --> 00:34:55,719
Baht?

308
00:35:01,040 --> 00:35:02,400
How much did you get?

309
00:35:02,480 --> 00:35:04,480
- No way.
- Let me see.

310
00:35:04,560 --> 00:35:06,160
Nobody reveals their payment amount.

311
00:35:06,840 --> 00:35:08,800
If I got more than you, it's fine.

312
00:35:08,880 --> 00:35:10,800
But if you got less than me,
that's fine too.

313
00:35:10,880 --> 00:35:11,800
Show me.

314
00:35:11,880 --> 00:35:13,040
- Just let me see.
- No.

315
00:35:13,120 --> 00:35:15,280
Let me see for a second.

316
00:35:15,360 --> 00:35:17,520
Let me see.

317
00:35:17,600 --> 00:35:18,520
Give it to me.

318
00:35:23,840 --> 00:35:25,600
Eat more, babe.

319
00:35:26,920 --> 00:35:28,920
I already ate kilos of this, babe.

320
00:35:29,000 --> 00:35:31,720
If I eat any more,
I'll turn into a grizzly bear.

321
00:35:34,200 --> 00:35:36,560
I just don't want you to leave.

322
00:35:37,080 --> 00:35:39,520
If you can still eat, then keep eating.

323
00:35:39,600 --> 00:35:40,920
I'll pay for everything.

324
00:35:42,080 --> 00:35:43,160
You about to burp?

325
00:35:49,200 --> 00:35:51,680
No matter what, I still have to go.

326
00:35:59,320 --> 00:36:01,280
Even though we've been together
for a few hours,

327
00:36:06,240 --> 00:36:08,080
I already love you.

328
00:36:08,160 --> 00:36:10,480
<i>Saranghae.</i>

329
00:36:12,200 --> 00:36:13,600
Incredible.

330
00:36:13,680 --> 00:36:16,720
<i>Saranghaeyo</i> too, babe.

331
00:36:18,320 --> 00:36:19,840
You've got something stuck in your hair.

332
00:36:22,040 --> 00:36:22,880
My heart?

333
00:36:27,600 --> 00:36:31,480
Babe, I'm taking your heart
with me too.

334
00:36:32,240 --> 00:36:34,160
Even if our love becomes long-distance,

335
00:36:34,240 --> 00:36:35,720
I'll never feel lonely.

336
00:36:35,800 --> 00:36:38,360
For you, I can endure anything.

337
00:36:39,400 --> 00:36:41,680
I probably won't ever find anyone as cute

338
00:36:41,760 --> 00:36:44,840
and clever as you again.

339
00:36:44,920 --> 00:36:46,920
And I'll never find anyone as tame

340
00:36:47,840 --> 00:36:49,760
as you either.

341
00:36:50,920 --> 00:36:51,800
Babe.

342
00:36:52,960 --> 00:36:57,280
We'll hear each other's heartbeats
forever.

343
00:37:06,440 --> 00:37:09,760
You've got a dog named Fried Chicken,
and now you're making fried chicken too?

344
00:37:10,280 --> 00:37:11,920
Looks like you love dogs
more than your girlfriend.

345
00:37:14,040 --> 00:37:15,640
Hey, what's wrong with you?

346
00:37:16,160 --> 00:37:17,640
Hey?

347
00:37:18,240 --> 00:37:19,600
Hey?

348
00:37:20,520 --> 00:37:21,360
The wind took me.

349
00:37:22,560 --> 00:37:24,760
Because Prapai means "wind", doesn't it?

350
00:37:26,800 --> 00:37:29,600
Don't joke like that again. You scared me.

351
00:37:30,800 --> 00:37:31,720
How about this?

352
00:37:31,800 --> 00:37:36,320
Then next time, maybe I should learn
how to make pie instead.

353
00:37:38,560 --> 00:37:39,840
Okay, I'm buying that joke.

354
00:37:39,920 --> 00:37:41,200
Okay?

355
00:37:42,320 --> 00:37:43,640
Oh?

356
00:37:43,720 --> 00:37:45,160
- Praya.
- Oh?

357
00:37:54,800 --> 00:37:56,120
Can you not go?

358
00:38:00,200 --> 00:38:03,720
You already have someone
taking good care of you in my place now.

359
00:38:05,600 --> 00:38:08,480
What's so good about that?
He still hasn't proposed.

360
00:38:08,560 --> 00:38:12,560
Oh? If he won't ask,
then you go ask him yourself.

361
00:38:13,440 --> 00:38:15,560
Crazy. How can you say that?

362
00:38:15,640 --> 00:38:17,200
I'm a woman.

363
00:38:17,280 --> 00:38:20,600
Then I guess
you'll just have to keep waiting.

364
00:38:20,680 --> 00:38:22,320
No. I won't wait.

365
00:38:22,400 --> 00:38:27,640
Praya, go play matchmaker
and ask for me instead.

366
00:38:29,720 --> 00:38:31,200
If I wait for him to do it himself,

367
00:38:31,280 --> 00:38:33,480
I'll probably die of old age first.

368
00:38:36,760 --> 00:38:37,840
Okay.

369
00:38:38,760 --> 00:38:41,040
But I don't know if he'll agree or not.

370
00:38:43,160 --> 00:38:45,080
Try saying no and see what happens.

371
00:38:48,800 --> 00:38:51,960
And tell him
I'm not serious about the dowry.

372
00:38:52,040 --> 00:38:54,640
He doesn't need to wait until he becomes
a commander. Captain is enough.

373
00:38:54,720 --> 00:38:57,560
I can support him. I'm rich.

374
00:38:59,360 --> 00:39:00,880
That serious?

375
00:39:06,280 --> 00:39:07,840
Please take good care of my sister.

376
00:39:09,600 --> 00:39:10,640
I will.

377
00:39:12,680 --> 00:39:14,520
And ask for a huge dowry too.

378
00:39:16,080 --> 00:39:17,360
She's rich.

379
00:39:17,440 --> 00:39:20,560
Come on, Praya, instead
of helping bring the price down,

380
00:39:21,800 --> 00:39:24,000
you're already taking
someone else's side over your sister.

381
00:39:26,600 --> 00:39:27,560
Hey.

382
00:39:28,520 --> 00:39:30,080
Be very happy.

383
00:39:30,920 --> 00:39:32,480
And if you ever have a little one,

384
00:39:34,240 --> 00:39:35,880
I'll come back to help babysit.

385
00:39:39,600 --> 00:39:40,560
I should get going now.

386
00:39:41,880 --> 00:39:44,200
- I'll get going now.
- Alright.

387
00:39:47,800 --> 00:39:49,160
Wait. I'll walk you out.

388
00:39:49,240 --> 00:39:50,760
I'll go too. Come on.

389
00:39:50,840 --> 00:39:52,560
Come this way.

390
00:40:14,800 --> 00:40:16,800
Babe, have you eaten yet?

391
00:40:18,200 --> 00:40:19,280
What did you say, babe?

392
00:40:22,640 --> 00:40:24,800
I asked if you've eaten yet!

393
00:40:25,440 --> 00:40:27,480
I'm going to play football
with my friends.

394
00:40:28,120 --> 00:40:30,720
Babe, we've been talking for a week now.

395
00:40:30,800 --> 00:40:34,200
If I ask one thing and you answer another,
how am I supposed to understand you?

396
00:40:34,280 --> 00:40:37,960
I'm already at the top of the mountain.
You still can't hear me?

397
00:40:38,920 --> 00:40:41,920
Of course, I miss you.
I miss you like always, babe.

398
00:40:42,000 --> 00:40:42,840
Hello?

399
00:40:45,320 --> 00:40:46,320
Hello?

400
00:40:46,400 --> 00:40:48,800
Hello? Babe?

401
00:40:48,880 --> 00:40:49,800
Yong.

402
00:40:52,440 --> 00:40:53,560
It's time.

403
00:40:53,640 --> 00:40:56,600
Okay. Hello, kids.

404
00:40:56,680 --> 00:40:57,520
Let's go.

405
00:40:57,600 --> 00:41:00,080
Let's go draw pictures.

406
00:41:00,160 --> 00:41:04,280
Come on. Follow Teacher Fahsai
and Teacher Yong.

407
00:42:01,120 --> 00:42:02,720
Okay.

408
00:42:04,280 --> 00:42:06,200
Today, we're going to draw pictures.

409
00:42:06,280 --> 00:42:09,080
Draw flowers, trees, or the sky,
anything you like.

410
00:42:09,160 --> 00:42:10,640
Once you finish coloring,
turn it in to me.

411
00:42:11,240 --> 00:42:12,760
Yes.

412
00:42:12,840 --> 00:42:15,120
Here, take one and pass the rest
to the person behind you.

413
00:42:15,200 --> 00:42:17,000
Keep one for yourself.

414
00:42:18,280 --> 00:42:19,680
Here are the colors.

415
00:42:19,760 --> 00:42:21,480
Share them, okay?

416
00:42:21,560 --> 00:42:23,400
- Alright.
- If you've got your coloring book

417
00:42:23,480 --> 00:42:25,760
and colors, go sit down.

418
00:42:25,840 --> 00:42:28,280
Once you have everything,
go sit down, everyone.

419
00:42:28,360 --> 00:42:30,760
You can sit down.

420
00:42:33,000 --> 00:42:34,200
You can start drawing.

421
00:42:35,400 --> 00:42:37,000
Draw anything you like.

422
00:42:38,840 --> 00:42:41,720
I'll come around
and see what you're drawing.

423
00:42:46,480 --> 00:42:49,520
- How are you, Ms. Fahsai?
- Yes?

424
00:42:50,040 --> 00:42:51,400
Are you feeling better now?

425
00:42:51,480 --> 00:42:53,240
Much better.

426
00:42:53,760 --> 00:42:57,600
I really made the right decision
coming here to work for the foundation.

427
00:42:58,680 --> 00:43:00,280
I get to be with such lovely children,

428
00:43:01,000 --> 00:43:04,400
surrounded by flowers and nature.

429
00:43:04,480 --> 00:43:05,680
Do you want to paint?

430
00:43:05,760 --> 00:43:07,360
- I feel so much more at peace.
- What color should I paint?

431
00:43:09,200 --> 00:43:13,280
You'd feel even more at peace
if that someone were here too.

432
00:43:15,360 --> 00:43:17,360
Let's not talk about that anymore.

433
00:43:18,000 --> 00:43:19,160
It's impossible.

434
00:43:20,480 --> 00:43:23,240
My family did so much to his family.

435
00:43:23,320 --> 00:43:25,760
He only wanted revenge
and payback. That's all.

436
00:43:27,160 --> 00:43:28,880
Is that really all?

437
00:43:29,560 --> 00:43:30,880
He already has someone he loves.

438
00:43:32,120 --> 00:43:34,040
And he loves her very much.

439
00:43:35,320 --> 00:43:37,360
He's happy with the person he loves.

440
00:43:39,760 --> 00:43:41,920
I'm happy with the work I do.

441
00:43:43,160 --> 00:43:44,880
Everything fits perfectly now.

442
00:43:46,960 --> 00:43:48,120
Okay.

443
00:43:49,120 --> 00:43:50,120
I can't see much.

444
00:43:51,440 --> 00:43:53,080
Let's see what everyone's drawing.

445
00:44:04,800 --> 00:44:05,640
Who are you drawing?

446
00:44:08,320 --> 00:44:11,120
I drew you, Teacher. You're cute,

447
00:44:11,800 --> 00:44:15,120
pretty, and kind, just like an angel.

448
00:44:16,560 --> 00:44:18,680
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

449
00:45:05,200 --> 00:45:08,280
Hello, babe, can you hear me?

450
00:45:08,360 --> 00:45:09,960
Where are you?

451
00:45:10,480 --> 00:45:13,280
I'm in your heart, babe.

452
00:45:15,160 --> 00:45:16,760
Crazy!

453
00:45:17,760 --> 00:45:19,400
Are you drunk?

454
00:45:19,920 --> 00:45:21,880
Drunk…

455
00:45:22,840 --> 00:45:27,160
Drunk in love with you. Be my girlfriend.

456
00:45:30,200 --> 00:45:32,040
Girlfriend?

457
00:45:32,120 --> 00:45:36,080
Someone like you has to be

458
00:45:36,160 --> 00:45:40,040
my future husband.

459
00:45:42,520 --> 00:45:43,520
Oh, babe.

460
00:45:44,600 --> 00:45:47,160
- What?
- An ant bit me.

461
00:45:47,240 --> 00:45:49,240
What's wrong?

462
00:45:49,320 --> 00:45:52,560
It's like I'm itching for you
every second.

463
00:45:53,840 --> 00:45:56,720
You mean you miss me every day?

464
00:45:58,400 --> 00:46:02,000
Why are you standing on that rock
twisting around like that?

465
00:46:03,000 --> 00:46:06,760
Because this spot has the best signal.

466
00:46:07,280 --> 00:46:08,160
Oh?

467
00:46:08,680 --> 00:46:12,360
Why can I hear you so clearly today?

468
00:46:12,440 --> 00:46:13,280
Because

469
00:46:13,920 --> 00:46:16,840
I came climbing after my heart.

470
00:46:24,760 --> 00:46:27,680
I came to find my heart, babe.

471
00:46:29,600 --> 00:46:31,600
- Babe.
- Babe.

472
00:46:32,240 --> 00:46:33,440
I'm here.

473
00:46:33,520 --> 00:46:35,320
Babe.

474
00:46:35,400 --> 00:46:36,440
Babe.

475
00:46:36,520 --> 00:46:38,680
I've missed you.

476
00:46:38,760 --> 00:46:40,640
Babe.

477
00:46:43,360 --> 00:46:44,440
Babe.

478
00:46:44,520 --> 00:46:47,600
I came all this way because I missed you.
I should get a reward.

479
00:46:59,680 --> 00:47:00,520
Babe.

480
00:47:01,480 --> 00:47:04,320
Babe, did you get lip filler?

481
00:47:04,400 --> 00:47:05,600
Where are your lips?

482
00:47:05,680 --> 00:47:07,120
I'm right here.

483
00:47:10,400 --> 00:47:12,480
- That was just your cheek?
- Yes.

484
00:47:12,560 --> 00:47:15,600
If that was your lips,
how amazing would that be, babe?

485
00:47:15,680 --> 00:47:16,960
You want to find out?

486
00:47:18,840 --> 00:47:20,720
Let's go.

487
00:47:31,440 --> 00:47:34,680
Teacher Fahsai, why has Teacher Yong
been in the bathroom for so long?

488
00:47:35,560 --> 00:47:37,240
She'll be back soon.

489
00:47:38,200 --> 00:47:40,120
Who's finished coloring? Let me see.

490
00:47:40,200 --> 00:47:41,520
Me.

491
00:47:42,040 --> 00:47:43,080
Let me see.

492
00:47:46,560 --> 00:47:49,000
And who's this man wearing a crown?

493
00:47:51,520 --> 00:47:53,120
An angel.

494
00:47:53,200 --> 00:47:56,840
You're an angel. He's an angel too.

495
00:47:58,760 --> 00:48:00,400
You mean that prince?

496
00:48:01,240 --> 00:48:04,160
He's secretly watching you, Teacher.
There he is.

497
00:48:35,760 --> 00:48:38,560
I saw you with the children,
so I didn't want to disturb you.

498
00:48:40,760 --> 00:48:43,160
I could only watch from afar.
I got carried away.

499
00:48:44,800 --> 00:48:47,480
See? He really
was watching for a long time.

500
00:48:48,200 --> 00:48:51,440
Yes. I saw it too.

501
00:48:55,800 --> 00:48:59,120
How have you been?

502
00:49:04,080 --> 00:49:05,440
You moved so far away.

503
00:49:06,960 --> 00:49:11,600
But this place is really beautiful.
It's such a nice place to live.

504
00:49:11,680 --> 00:49:12,800
Can I live here too?

505
00:49:17,480 --> 00:49:18,320
Everyone,

506
00:49:20,320 --> 00:49:22,480
does Teacher Fahsai understand Thai?

507
00:49:23,080 --> 00:49:24,760
I asked her something,
but she won't answer me.

508
00:49:24,840 --> 00:49:27,680
Can you help ask her for me?

509
00:49:27,760 --> 00:49:30,280
Yes.

510
00:49:30,360 --> 00:49:32,680
Ask Teacher Fahsai if she's been well.

511
00:49:32,760 --> 00:49:35,920
He's asking if you've been well!

512
00:49:37,240 --> 00:49:38,960
Ask if I can live here too.

513
00:49:39,040 --> 00:49:41,840
Can he live here too?

514
00:49:43,800 --> 00:49:45,840
Ask why she won't answer.

515
00:49:45,920 --> 00:49:48,120
Why won't you answer?

516
00:49:50,760 --> 00:49:54,200
Everyone, hurry and finish your drawings.
I need to take care of something first.

517
00:49:55,080 --> 00:49:57,520
When I come back,
you have to turn in your pictures, okay?

518
00:49:57,600 --> 00:49:59,040
Yes.

519
00:49:59,120 --> 00:50:00,600
Fahsai. Fahsai, wait.

520
00:50:05,680 --> 00:50:08,120
Fahsai.

521
00:50:11,560 --> 00:50:14,920
Hey, where are you running off to?

522
00:50:15,000 --> 00:50:17,440
You know you can't run away from me.

523
00:50:18,040 --> 00:50:19,240
What else do you want from me?

524
00:50:20,280 --> 00:50:22,560
I have nothing left for you
to take from me anymore.

525
00:50:26,080 --> 00:50:27,080
Your heart.

526
00:50:31,440 --> 00:50:32,840
I have to win it back.

527
00:50:36,240 --> 00:50:37,240
My heart belongs to me.

528
00:50:38,480 --> 00:50:40,960
I won't let you hurt it again.

529
00:50:42,920 --> 00:50:45,080
Everything that happened before,
consider it my repayment

530
00:50:45,600 --> 00:50:47,200
because you once saved my life.

531
00:50:49,120 --> 00:50:51,280
But from now on,
we owe each other nothing.

532
00:50:52,320 --> 00:50:53,280
Wait.

533
00:50:55,240 --> 00:50:56,480
What debt are you talking about?

534
00:50:58,240 --> 00:51:01,520
I lied to you all along.

535
00:51:04,360 --> 00:51:05,880
I hurt you.

536
00:51:06,680 --> 00:51:08,200
I hurt your family.

537
00:51:09,160 --> 00:51:10,720
I know I was wrong.

538
00:51:13,600 --> 00:51:14,640
I'm sorry.

539
00:51:25,680 --> 00:51:27,240
I have to apologize too.

540
00:51:29,120 --> 00:51:32,000
For what my father
and brother did to your family.

541
00:51:34,160 --> 00:51:37,120
Everything happened
without me knowing anything.

542
00:51:43,200 --> 00:51:44,360
But…

543
00:51:45,160 --> 00:51:47,360
Dad and Samut already paid for their sins

544
00:51:48,360 --> 00:51:49,840
with their lives.

545
00:51:53,480 --> 00:51:56,040
Everything should end now.

546
00:51:58,280 --> 00:52:00,880
You can finally be happy
with the person you love.

547
00:52:07,120 --> 00:52:09,000
The person I love?

548
00:52:15,520 --> 00:52:17,360
You mean Maysa?

549
00:52:20,560 --> 00:52:23,680
Yes. I admit I loved May very much.

550
00:52:28,960 --> 00:52:30,280
Wait.

551
00:52:34,840 --> 00:52:36,080
But that's in the past.

552
00:52:37,480 --> 00:52:41,240
I'm not the same Peeraka anymore.
I'm Wayu.

553
00:52:42,840 --> 00:52:47,040
Wayu, who loves only you, Fahsai.

554
00:53:01,120 --> 00:53:04,120
Can we forget the past

555
00:53:06,560 --> 00:53:08,040
and start over?

556
00:53:17,760 --> 00:53:19,960
You're still wearing our wedding ring.

557
00:53:24,920 --> 00:53:26,000
It was expensive.

558
00:53:27,160 --> 00:53:28,200
I didn't want to waste it.

559
00:53:31,560 --> 00:53:33,360
Fahsai.

560
00:53:34,080 --> 00:53:36,120
Let's talk this through first.

561
00:53:36,200 --> 00:53:37,840
Where are you going?

562
00:53:38,840 --> 00:53:39,880
Hey.

563
00:53:40,640 --> 00:53:43,080
Fahsai, wait.

564
00:53:58,040 --> 00:54:00,720
Yong, where are you taking the kids?

565
00:54:00,800 --> 00:54:03,120
To have snacks.

566
00:54:05,840 --> 00:54:08,000
It's only nine o'clock.
What break is this?

567
00:54:08,080 --> 00:54:11,320
Nine o'clock is still a break time.

568
00:54:11,400 --> 00:54:15,280
But this break is so someone around here
can confess their love.

569
00:54:18,840 --> 00:54:19,680
Alright, kids.

570
00:54:19,760 --> 00:54:22,760
Anyone who wants more snacks or ice cream,

571
00:54:22,840 --> 00:54:25,240
follow me.

572
00:54:25,320 --> 00:54:26,640
Babe,

573
00:54:26,720 --> 00:54:28,720
I want a dozen kids like this.

574
00:54:28,800 --> 00:54:31,400
Just say the word, babe. I can do it.

575
00:54:33,160 --> 00:54:34,400
I've got plenty of energy.

576
00:54:35,720 --> 00:54:38,320
Anyone who can sing
the chicken song, sing along. Let's go.

577
00:54:44,320 --> 00:54:45,720
Why is this happening?

578
00:54:45,800 --> 00:54:47,240
- Wait.
- Alright.

579
00:54:47,320 --> 00:54:48,160
Hey.

580
00:54:48,240 --> 00:54:50,280
Let go. Someone might see us.

581
00:54:51,280 --> 00:54:52,760
Who's going to see?

582
00:54:52,840 --> 00:54:54,640
It's just the two of us here.

583
00:54:56,280 --> 00:54:57,680
Let go.

584
00:55:01,720 --> 00:55:04,920
I missed you so much. So much.

585
00:55:09,160 --> 00:55:10,560
I missed you every day.

586
00:55:13,400 --> 00:55:14,520
What about you?

587
00:55:16,000 --> 00:55:18,520
Did you miss me at all?

588
00:55:21,360 --> 00:55:22,840
How could I,

589
00:55:24,760 --> 00:55:27,560
when I knew full well that you
and May loved each other?

590
00:55:36,280 --> 00:55:37,960
The past is the past.

591
00:55:39,440 --> 00:55:41,800
I thought you were going abroad with May.

592
00:55:43,000 --> 00:55:46,440
I saw Maysa off
at the airport as a friend.

593
00:55:47,280 --> 00:55:49,880
Do you know what I did after that?

594
00:55:53,600 --> 00:55:56,200
I trained Prapai and Captain Anawin

595
00:55:56,920 --> 00:55:58,920
so they could run the company,

596
00:55:59,880 --> 00:56:01,680
because I'm coming to live here with you.

597
00:56:01,760 --> 00:56:04,280
Do you have somewhere for me to sleep?

598
00:56:08,040 --> 00:56:10,400
The foundation has no openings.

599
00:56:12,160 --> 00:56:14,760
That's fine. I can work for free.

600
00:56:14,840 --> 00:56:16,400
I'll treat the villagers for free too.

601
00:56:16,920 --> 00:56:18,440
Then find somewhere else to sleep.

602
00:56:22,000 --> 00:56:24,400
What? My wife has a house.

603
00:56:24,480 --> 00:56:26,240
Why would I sleep somewhere else?

604
00:56:26,920 --> 00:56:28,840
Does that make any sense?

605
00:56:29,520 --> 00:56:31,880
- No.
- You're actually funny.

606
00:56:34,160 --> 00:56:35,760
I'm sleeping at my wife's house.

607
00:56:36,520 --> 00:56:37,400
Hey.

608
00:56:50,800 --> 00:56:51,960
I like it so much.

609
00:56:54,960 --> 00:56:57,200
I like seeing you laugh.

610
00:56:59,320 --> 00:57:00,960
I like seeing you smile.

611
00:57:03,320 --> 00:57:04,400
When you're angry,

612
00:57:05,400 --> 00:57:08,400
when you sulk, when you cry,

613
00:57:09,760 --> 00:57:11,360
when you're happy.

614
00:57:12,200 --> 00:57:13,840
I love everything about you.

615
00:57:17,400 --> 00:57:18,640
I love you.

616
00:57:35,080 --> 00:57:37,600
I want to hold you
like this for a long time.

617
00:57:41,240 --> 00:57:42,600
I don't want to let go.

618
00:57:48,240 --> 00:57:49,760
You don't have to love me.

619
00:57:52,520 --> 00:57:54,800
I can love you enough for the both of us.

620
00:58:09,760 --> 00:58:12,000
I tried to get over you,

621
00:58:14,720 --> 00:58:16,240
but I couldn't.

622
00:58:19,000 --> 00:58:22,760
I thought if you were happy with May,

623
00:58:24,840 --> 00:58:26,480
I'd be happy too.

624
00:58:30,280 --> 00:58:31,480
But no.

625
00:58:33,480 --> 00:58:34,800
I was miserable.

626
00:58:38,400 --> 00:58:40,600
And I missed you more every day.

627
00:58:45,000 --> 00:58:46,560
Thank you for coming back.

628
00:58:49,560 --> 00:58:52,400
Thank you for letting me
start loving you all over again.

629
00:59:04,000 --> 00:59:05,040
Thank you.

630
00:59:07,640 --> 00:59:10,360
Thank you for giving
this man another chance.

631
00:59:46,960 --> 00:59:49,160
You have to start
winning my heart all over again.

632
00:59:54,600 --> 00:59:55,680
I will.

633
00:59:57,000 --> 00:59:58,440
I'll do it every day.

634
01:00:32,920 --> 01:00:38,640
THE END

635
01:01:33,000 --> 01:01:35,160
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
